    <item>
      <title>Mälkki &amp; Josefowicz in Helsinki</title>
      <link>https://walse.cz/koncert/20220916-helsinki-bruckner/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 16 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://walse.cz/koncert/20220916-helsinki-bruckner/</guid>
      <description>&lt;table&gt;
  &lt;thead&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Susanna Mälkki&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;conductor&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Leila Josefowicz&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;violin&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;John Adams&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Violin Concerto&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Anton Bruckner&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Symphony No. 4 &amp;ldquo;Romantic&amp;rdquo; (1878/1880)&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last autumn, the Los Angeles Times lauded violinist Leila Josefowicz’s performance of John Adams’ Violin Concerto: “A daring, probing, thinking, dancing, spectacularly virtuosic soloist… she played each turn of phrase, each gesture, as though it were a new thought or feeling that suddenly astonished her” (Los Angeles Times, 9.11.2021).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good news for lovers of mysticism and mysteries! The Helsinki Philharmonic Orchestra will perform no less than three symphonies by Anton Bruckner this season. The series begins with one of his most popular, the 4th Symphony – a mysterious relation to ancient tales.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
